parameters.description: Half-saturation constant for nutrient effect on COTS larval survival (Michaelis-Menten kinetics). Represents nutrient level at which larval survival enhancement is 50% of maximum. Lower values mean outbreaks triggered by smaller nutrient pulses. NOTE: Currently not active until nutrient_dat is provided.
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Nutrient concentration for half-maximal larval survival effect

parameters.description: Maximum multiplicative effect of nutrients on COTS recruitment. Value of 3.0 means nutrients can triple recruitment success under optimal conditions. This parameter controls outbreak magnitude triggered by nutrient pulses. NOTE: Currently not active until nutrient_dat is provided.
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Maximum fold-increase in recruitment from nutrient enrichment
